statement.markdown:
Given a CSS string with grid layout properties, fix the bug that prevents the grid from displaying correctly. The string represents a CSS class definition with grid container properties. You need to analyze the string, identify the bug, and modify the code to display the grid correctly.

Example Input:

```.container {
  display: inline-grid;
  grid-template-columns: 100px 200px;
  grid-template-rows: 100px;
}
```

The grid container should display two columns of different widths and one row. However, due to the bug, it only displays one column and one row.

Input Format:

A string representing a CSS class definition with grid container properties.

Output Format:

The modified CSS string with the bug fixed.

Notes:

The grid container should display two columns of different widths and one row.

You can assume the input string is well-formed and does not contain any syntax errors.

